Do a global search for "is":

Copy
let str = "this is a test?";
let patt1 = /is/g;
let result = str.match(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:


Description
The g modifier can do a global match , find all matches rather than stopping after the first match.

To perform a global, case-insensitive search, use g modifier together with the "i" modifier.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
g	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
new RegExp("regexp", "g") or simply: /regexp/g
More Examples
Do a global, case-insensitive search for "is":

Copy
let str = "This is Is iS a test?";
let patt1 = /is/gi;
let result = str.match(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:
